This challenge is about time trace debugging using windbg.
Its like record the process execution of a exe. Capture the stuff like pcap of a wireshark.
Follow the guide on how to set up.
Download the windbg preview on Windows 10, open trace file. 

Challenge talks about some keylogging stuff, popular windows API for keylogging = TranslateMessage.

Solution:
Set a breakpoint after TranslateMessage and read the RAX returned.
RAX is a message structure. 
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winuser/ns-winuser-msg
In the structure, first value is the HWND, second value = message (0x100 = KEY_DOWN, 0x101 = KEY_UP), third value is the virtual character
What we are interested in is the third character. Link below will translate the character
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/inputdev/virtual-key-codes


Breakpoint command: breaks after translateMessage, if the return value is not 0. then print the value of the third param and continue. 
bp 00007ff9`71610d31 ".if (rax > 0) {.printf \"%p\n\", poi(00007ff6f91c1278+8+8); g} .else {gc}"
